            <title>[CASSANDRA-18677] BTI format&apos;s decision to preload partition index is incorrect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18677</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On load, BTI format SSTables are supposed to walk through the partition index when the SSTable does not have a bloom filter, to prefetch the index in cache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This decision &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/io/sstable/format/bti/BtiTableReaderLoadingBuilder.java#L125C62-L125C62&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;is currently inverted&lt;/a&gt;, causing both an unnecessary preload when a filter is present, and making filterless sstables inefficient.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
